        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(telegram): send voice typing cue before transcription",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Send the initial Telegram direct-chat typing cue for audio-only voice messages before inbound body resolution starts audio transcription.\n- Move configured binding readiness ahead of body/STT work so unavailable configured bindings do not emit preflight typing cues.\n- Add and fix a typing-order regression test that proves `sendChatAction(\"typing\")` runs before `transcribeFirstAudio` for voice-only direct messages.\n\nFixes #58887.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.typing.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.body.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Telegram direct-chat voice messages now emit the first typing cue before audio transcription starts, so the sender gets immediate activity feedback during potentially slow STT work.\n\nReal environment tested: Local full OpenClaw checkout on PR branch `codex/telegram-voice-preflight-typing-58887-20260618`, exercising Telegram message-context construction and the voice preflight typing path through the repository extension-telegram Vitest harness after the patch.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.typing.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.body.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message.test.ts --reporter=verbose\ngit diff --check origin/main...HEAD\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: Terminal capture from the focused Telegram run showed the voice typing/transcription ordering path passing:\n\n```text\n✓ |extension-telegram| extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.typing.test.ts > buildTelegramMessageContext typing > sends direct typing before voice transcription starts\n✓ |extension-telegram| extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.typing.test.ts > buildTelegramMessageContext typing > does not send early direct typing before DM access passes\n✓ |extension-telegram| extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.body.test.ts > resolveTelegramInboundBody > transcribes DM voice notes via preflight (not only groups)\n\nTest Files  3 passed (3)\nTests  38 passed (38)\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 5.42s\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The focused tests verify `sendChatAction(\"typing\")` is emitted once before `transcribeFirstAudio` for a voice-only direct message, access-denied DMs do not emit the early cue, and existing Telegram body/message processor behavior remains green. `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD` produced no output.\n\nWhat was not tested: A live Telegram bot with real Telegram credentials was not started in this environment; the focused Telegram context/body/processor tests exercise the changed runtime ordering without external network credentials.\n",
